1. Create a project by name Employee Management System(Employee Management System)
2. Create a package by name admin
3. Create a class name by name Employee, use java bean class structure
	consider id as private and final
	initialize through parameterized constructor
4. Create a package by name repository
5. Create a class by name EmployeeCreation in admin package
	This class should have static method by name create
		1. parameters name, salary, and exp
		2. return type must be Employee class type
		
		this method should create Employee object and return it
6. Create a class by name EmployeeDB in repository package
	It should initialize by size of the array
	It should contain method by name addEmployee
		parameters Employee type
		add those in empdb array
	It should contain method by name viewEmployeeRecords